	+asset('SuburbanWatch-Asset','<b>Oracle Stone:</b> A mystical scrying gem. At the beginning of each mystery, you may consult it—ask any question. The Keeper will answer with something true and useful, but they may make the answer difficult to understand.',2)
	+asset('SuburbanWatch-Asset','<b>Individual Transport:</b> A regular car, motorbike, or bicycle for every team member.',1)
	+asset('SuburbanWatch-Asset','<b>SWG Radio Network:</b> A set of devices that allow you to easily talk to the rest of the SWG (as well as the base stations at your homes/the SWG headquarters).',1)
	+asset('SuburbanWatch-Asset','<b>Headquarters:</b> A relatively secure space to use as a base. There’s room for all your monster hunting gear and books, maybe even space to sleep and a kitchen.',2)
	+asset('SuburbanWatch-Asset','<b>Sacred Site:</b> A place outdoors that has a reservoir of magical power. The Keeper always considers this site when a magical ritual requires a particular place.',2)
	+asset('SuburbanWatch-Asset','<b>Workshop:</b> A big space for craft and repair projects, with plenty of tools and materials.',1)
	+asset('SuburbanWatch-Asset','<b>Infirmary:</b> You have access to a doctor’s surgery or other suitable first aid office. You may use it for regular treatment of injuries, no questions asked.',1)
	+asset('SuburbanWatch-Asset','<b>Innocent Front:</b> You have access to a regular business or institution. This means that your monster hunting hijinks can be concealed to an extent from your friends, family, and colleagues. For example: a cafe, a library, an antique store, etc.',1)
	+asset('SuburbanWatch-Asset','<b>Regular Jobs:</b> You have access to a place of employment for any of the hunters who need it. You earn enough to cover regular day-to-day expenses, and there’s time to fit in monster hunting around your hours.',1)
